            "text": "{\"total_count\":11,\"incomplete_results\":false,\"items\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22\",\"id\":4371367273,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBI3FaQ\",\"number\":22,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-local): create apps/mcp-local — publishable npm binary that runs stdio MCP\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:15:35Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:59:08Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:59:08Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nCreate \\\\`apps/mcp-local/\\\\` — the v1 CLI binary. Wires \\\\`@slopweaver/db\\\\` + \\\\`@slopweaver/mcp-server\\\\` together and exposes the \\\\`slopweaver\\\\` command. **This is the MVP milestone**: after this PR, a user can run \\\\`claude mcp add slopweaver -- npx -y @slopweaver/mcp-local\\\\` (or after publish, \\\\`slopweaver\\\\`) and call \\\\`ping\\\\` from any MCP client.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] \\\\`apps/mcp-local/package.json\\\\`: \\\\`name: \\\\\\\"@slopweaver/mcp-local\\\\\\\"\\\\` (or final name TBD), \\\\`bin: { slopweaver: \\\\\\\"./dist/cli.js\\\\\\\" }\\\\`, marked \\\\`\\\\\\\"private\\\\\\\": false\\\\` ready for npm publish\\n- [ ] \\\\`apps/mcp-local/src/cli.ts\\\\` — entry point: parses minimal args (\\\\`--version\\\\`, \\\\`--help\\\\`), opens DB at \\\\`~/.slopweaver/slopweaver.db\\\\`, registers \\\\`ping\\\\` tool, calls \\\\`startStdio()\\\\`\\n- [ ] Default behavior with no args = run stdio MCP server (so \\\\`slopweaver\\\\` works as the bin command for \\\\`claude mcp add\\\\`)\\n- [ ] Bundled with esbuild or tsup into \\\\`dist/cli.js\\\\` so npm consumers don't need TypeScript\\n- [ ] Smoke test: an integration test that spawns the built CLI, sends an MCP \\\\`tools/list\\\\` request over stdio, asserts \\\\`ping\\\\` is listed\\n- [ ] README install snippet updated: \\\\`claude mcp add slopweaver -- npx -y @slopweaver/mcp-local\\\\` (replaces the misleading \\\\`slopweaver token create\\\\` flow per #11)\\n- [ ] \\\\`pnpm validate\\\\` green\\n- [ ] **Out of scope**: \\\\`init\\\\` / \\\\`doctor\\\\` / \\\\`connect\\\\` subcommands (later issues), web UI (later issue), real integrations (later issues)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n- Depends on: #19 (contracts), #20 (db), #21 (mcp-server)\\n- This is **the v1 MVP**. After this lands, the install story works in Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, Cline.\\n- Decision: #11 (stdio-only)\\n- Roadmap update: #2 — replaces the \\\\\\\"localhost:60701 with stdio + HTTP\\\\\\\" plan with stdio-only\\n- After this PR, file follow-up issues for: init/doctor/connect commands (#23-ish), web UI (#24-ish), MCP Registry submission\\n\\n## AI prompt\\n\\n\\\\`/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/[N]\\\\`\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/22/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21\",\"id\":4371366735,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBI3DTw\",\"number\":21,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-server): scaffold @slopweaver/mcp-server with stdio transport + ping tool\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:15:16Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:13:47Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:13:47Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nCreate \\\\`packages/mcp-server/\\\\` — the framework-agnostic MCP server. v1 ships **stdio transport only** (no HTTP, no auth) per #11. Includes a tool registry and the \\\\`ping\\\\` tool as the smoke-test surface.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] Uses \\\\`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\\\\` from the **\\\\`v1.x\\\\` line, not \\\\`main\\\\`** (\\\\`main\\\\` is pre-alpha v2)\\n- [ ] \\\\`packages/mcp-server/src/server.ts\\\\` exports \\\\`createMcpServer({ db, tools })\\\\` returning a configured MCP \\\\`Server\\\\` instance\\n- [ ] \\\\`packages/mcp-server/src/tools/registry.ts\\\\` — typed tool registry; tools register a Zod input schema (from \\\\`@slopweaver/contracts\\\\`) + handler\\n- [ ] \\\\`packages/mcp-server/src/tools/builtin/ping.ts\\\\` — \\\\`ping\\\\` tool returns \\\\`{ ok: true, version, uptime_s }\\\\`\\n- [ ] Stdio transport wiring (\\\\`StdioServerTransport\\\\`) but exposed via a \\\\`startStdio()\\\\` helper so the app layer owns lifecycle\\n- [ ] Vitest test that registers \\\\`ping\\\\`, sends a tool-call request through an in-memory transport, asserts response shape\\n- [ ] No \\\\`@nestjs/*\\\\` imports\\n- [ ] No HTTP transport, no bearer-auth middleware, no token verification — stdio-only per #11\\n- [ ] \\\\`pnpm validate\\\\` green\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n- Depends on: #19 (contracts), #20 (db)\\n- Sequential precondition for: #22 (mcp-local app wires this)\\n- Decision: #11 (stdio-only, no MCP-layer auth)\\n- SDK target: \\\\`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\\\\` \\\\`v1.x\\\\` per [SDK README](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk)\\n- Composite tools (start_session etc) live under \\\\`src/tools/composite/\\\\` per CLAUDE.md — out of scope for this PR\\n\\n## AI prompt\\n\\n\\\\`/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/[N]\\\\`\\n\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/21/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23\",\"id\":4371367689,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBI3HCQ\",\"number\":23,\"title\":\"docs: rewrite README install snippet for stdio MCP flow (post-#11)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842289148,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkAz_A\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/documentation\",\"name\":\"documentation\",\"color\":\"0075ca\",\"default\":true,\"description\":\"Improvements or additions to documentation\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:15:49Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:00:27Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:00:27Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nThe README's install instructions are now misleading. They show \\\\`slopweaver token create\\\\` and instruct the user to paste a token into \\\\`~/.claude.json\\\\`. Per the resolution of #11, v1 ships stdio-only with no MCP-layer auth — no token paste required.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] Replace the \\\\\\\"Install (coming with v1.0.0)\\\\\\\" section with the stdio flow:\\n  \\\\`\\\\`\\\\`bash\\n  claude mcp add slopweaver -- npx -y @slopweaver/mcp-local\\n  # then: ask Claude Code about your work\\n  \\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n  Plus equivalent for Cursor / Codex / Cline once known\\n- [ ] Drop the \\\\\\\"Then add the printed MCP token to \\\\`~/.claude.json\\\\`\\\\\\\" line\\n- [ ] Update integration list to mention v1 = GitHub + Slack only (matches roadmap)\\n- [ ] Add a short note: \\\\\\\"User-to-GitHub auth uses GitHub's OAuth/PAT — that's separate from MCP transport\\\\\\\"\\n- [ ] No mention of OAuth 2.1 / PAT / \\\\`slopweaver token create\\\\` in the install path\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n- Decision: #11 (closed; stdio-only)\\n- Roadmap update: #2 (post-#11 amendments comment)\\n- This can land in parallel with #19-22; it's a doc-only change\\n- **Don't reference packages that don't exist yet** (e.g. \\\\`@slopweaver/mcp-local\\\\` may need to be on npm before the README points at it; if it isn't, link to a \\\\\\\"coming soon\\\\\\\" install)\\n\\n## AI prompt\\n\\n\\\\`/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/[N]\\\\`\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/23/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10\",\"id\":4367851239,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBFge5w\",\"number\":10,\"title\":\"Scaffolding & DevOps tracking\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930893,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-zQ\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/scaffolding\",\"name\":\"scaffolding\",\"color\":\"1d76db\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"Repo scaffolding / DevOps / AI orchestration work\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestone/1\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1/labels\",\"id\":15768380,\"node_id\":\"MI_kwDOSSFOvc4A8Js8\",\"number\":1,\"title\":\"v1.0.0\",\"description\":\"First public release of SlopWeaver. Help Claude Code answer 'what should I work on next?' by searching across your work tools. See tracking issue for the full checklist.\",\"creator\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"open_issues\":2,\"closed_issues\":1,\"state\":\"open\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:32Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:22Z\",\"due_on\":null,\"closed_at\":null},\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:09:34Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:40:39Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"> Sub-track of the [v1.0.0 roadmap](#2). Focused on AI-orchestration scaffolding, CLI tools, and DevOps work — the things that make every other PR easier.\\n\\n## Done already\\n\\n- [x] Repo created public, MIT, branch protection on \\\\`main\\\\`\\n- [x] \\\\`README.md\\\\`, \\\\`CLAUDE.md\\\\`, \\\\`SECURITY.md\\\\` (#1)\\n- [x] \\\\`CONTRIBUTING.md\\\\`, \\\\`CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md\\\\`, issue templates, PR template (#4)\\n- [x] Workspace bootstrap — \\\\`pnpm-workspace.yaml\\\\`, \\\\`turbo.json\\\\`, \\\\`tsconfig.base.json\\\\`, \\\\`biome.json\\\\`, \\\\`eslint.config.js\\\\` (#5)\\n- [x] CI workflow — GitHub Actions running format:check + lint + compile + test on every PR (#6)\\n- [x] \\\\`@slopweaver/cli-tools\\\\` first package + \\\\`pnpm cli worktree new\\\\` subcommand (#8)\\n- [x] \\\\`.claude/\\\\` orchestration scaffolding — slash commands, rules, settings (#9)\\n- [x] \\\\`task.yml\\\\` and \\\\`decision_record.yml\\\\` issue templates (#9)\\n- [x] \\\\`docs/contributing/ai-workflow.md\\\\` explaining the loop (#9)\\n- [x] \\\\`decision-record\\\\`, \\\\`task\\\\`, \\\\`scaffolding\\\\` labels created\\n- [x] npm name \\\\`slopweaver\\\\` reserved (v0.0.0 stub published)\\n\\n## Next on this track (one issue per item once filed)\\n\\n### Decisions to make first\\n\\n- [ ] Decision: OAuth 2.1 vs PAT for v1 auth model\\n- [ ] Decision: should v1 ship a publishable \\\\`@slopweaver/cli-tools\\\\` or keep it private?\\n- [ ] Decision: telemetry endpoint — own service vs PostHog Cloud vs strip from v1?\\n\\n### Scaffolding follow-ups\\n\\n- [x] Add \\\\`pnpm cli doctor\\\\` subcommand (Node version, pnpm version, port 60701, data dir) (#16)\\n- [ ] Add \\\\`pnpm cli connect-local\\\\` subcommand (deferred from PR #8 — rebuilt simpler than the private version, GitHub-only initially)\\n- [x] Add Vitest config + first unit tests for cli-tools (sanitiseTaskName has obvious test cases) (#16)\\n- [x] Add Knip config + \\\\`pnpm knip\\\\` script for unused-export detection (#17)\\n- [x] Add \\\\`pnpm validate\\\\` script that runs everything CI runs (one-shot pre-push check) (#17)\\n\\n### DevOps\\n\\n- [ ] GitHub Actions: Dependabot config for weekly dep bumps\\n- [x] GitHub Actions: \\\\`release.yml\\\\` for npm publish on tag (when there's something to publish) (#14)\\n- [ ] GitHub Actions: matrix-test on macOS + Linux + WSL (when there's code that's OS-sensitive)\\n- [ ] Set up GitHub Sponsors (apply now; lead time)\\n- [ ] Set up GitHub OAuth App for SlopWeaver Local (callback \\\\`http://localhost:60701/oauth/github/callback\\\\`)\\n\\n### Polish (lower priority)\\n\\n- [x] Add \\\\`.editorconfig\\\\` for non-Biome editors (#17)\\n- [ ] Add badges to README (CI status, npm version when published, license already there)\\n- [ ] Open GitHub Discussions categories (Q&A, Show and tell, Ideas)\\n\\n## How to pick up an item\\n\\nEach item above becomes its own issue (created lazily when work starts). Open it with the \\\\`task\\\\` template, copy the embedded \\\\`/fix-issue\\\\` prompt into Claude Code, agent picks it up.\\n\\nFor decisions, use the \\\\`decision_record\\\\` template; deliberate in comments; close with the resolution.\\n\\n\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/10/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20\",\"id\":4371366186,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBI3BKg\",\"number\":20,\"title\":\"feat(db): scaffold @slopweaver/db with Drizzle SQLite + initial migrations\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:14:59Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:29:50Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:29:50Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nCreate \\\\`packages/db/\\\\` with Drizzle ORM + better-sqlite3 and the initial schemas for v1 (no MCP-token table per #11). Includes migration tooling (\\\\`pnpm drizzle-kit generate\\\\`) and a connection helper.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] \\\\`packages/db/src/schema/\\\\` defines: \\\\`evidence_log\\\\`, \\\\`identity_graph\\\\`, \\\\`integration_state\\\\` (per-platform last-poll + cursor), \\\\`workspaces\\\\` (single-row for v1)\\n- [ ] Initial migration generated via \\\\`pnpm drizzle-kit generate\\\\` (NOT hand-written) and committed under \\\\`packages/db/migrations/\\\\`\\n- [ ] \\\\`createDb({ path })\\\\` helper that opens better-sqlite3 + applies pending migrations\\n- [ ] Default DB path: \\\\`~/.slopweaver/slopweaver.db\\\\` (XDG-aware: respect \\\\`XDG_DATA_HOME\\\\` if set)\\n- [ ] Vitest test that opens an in-memory DB, runs migrations, inserts and reads an \\\\`evidence_log\\\\` row\\n- [ ] \\\\`pnpm validate\\\\` green\\n- [ ] **No \\\\`packages/auth/\\\\` table** (mcp_tokens dropped per #11)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n- Depends on: #19 (contracts) for shared types\\n- Sequential precondition for: #20 (mcp-server), #22+ (integrations)\\n- Drizzle migration rule: tool-generated only, never manually written\\n- Refs decision: #11 (no MCP token table); roadmap update on #2\\n\\n## AI prompt\\n\\n\\\\`/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/[N]\\\\`\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/20/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19\",\"id\":4371365774,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBI2_jg\",\"number\":19,\"title\":\"feat(contracts): scaffold @slopweaver/contracts with Zod tool schemas\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:14:45Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:49:11Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:49:11Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nFlesh out the existing \\\\`packages/contracts/\\\\` stub with Zod schemas for the v1 MCP tool inputs/outputs and shared domain types. This is the type spine the rest of the packages depend on.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] \\\\`packages/contracts/src/index.ts\\\\` exports Zod schemas for: \\\\`PingArgs\\\\`, \\\\`PingResult\\\\`, \\\\`Reference\\\\` (URL or canonical ID), \\\\`Freshness\\\\` (per-integration last-poll + stale flag), \\\\`EvidenceLogEntry\\\\`, \\\\`StartSessionArgs\\\\`, \\\\`StartSessionResult\\\\`\\n- [ ] Schemas use named-object inputs (no positional args) per CLAUDE.md\\n- [ ] Strict mode TypeScript; \\\\`noUncheckedIndexedAccess\\\\`; no \\\\`any\\\\`\\n- [ ] Vitest unit tests for at least one schema's \\\\`safeParse\\\\` happy + sad path\\n- [ ] \\\\`pnpm validate\\\\` green (format/lint/compile/test/knip)\\n- [ ] No app or other-package imports — \\\\`@slopweaver/contracts\\\\` is a leaf\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n- Existing stub: \\\\`packages/contracts/\\\\` (no \\\\`src/\\\\` yet)\\n- Use ts-rest only if it pulls weight; pure Zod is fine for v1\\n- Schema source-of-truth lives here; \\\\`packages/db/\\\\` will derive Drizzle tables from these where useful, \\\\`packages/mcp-server/\\\\` will use them for tool registration\\n- Decision background: #11 (stdio-only v1, no auth surface in contracts)\\n- This is **PR 1 of 15** in the v1 plan. Sequential precondition for #19 (db), #20 (mcp-server), #21 (mcp-local).\\n\\n## AI prompt\\n\\n\\\\`/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/[N]\\\\`\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/19/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2\",\"id\":4367592734,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBFQtHg\",\"number\":2,\"title\":\"v1.0.0 roadmap\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestone/1\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1/labels\",\"id\":15768380,\"node_id\":\"MI_kwDOSSFOvc4A8Js8\",\"number\":1,\"title\":\"v1.0.0\",\"description\":\"First public release of SlopWeaver. Help Claude Code answer 'what should I work on next?' by searching across your work tools. See tracking issue for the full checklist.\",\"creator\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"open_issues\":2,\"closed_issues\":1,\"state\":\"open\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:32Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:22Z\",\"due_on\":null,\"closed_at\":null},\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:25:23Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:38Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"> Canonical public roadmap for v1.0.0 of SlopWeaver. Pinned to the repo so contributors and curious onlookers can see what's being built. Each checkbox links to its own sub-issue (or PR) as work progresses.\\n\\n**Status**: pre-alpha. v1.0.0 ships when the items below are all done. No fixed date — ships when ready.\\n\\n**v1.0.0 hook**: _Help Claude Code answer \\\"what should I work on next?\\\" by searching across your work tools._ See [README](../blob/main/README.md) for the demo scenario.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## CLI commands\\n\\n- [ ] `npx -y slopweaver@latest init` — first-run interactive setup\\n- [ ] `slopweaver doctor` — diagnostic checks (the onboarding UI when something fails)\\n- [ ] `slopweaver connect github` — GitHub fine-grained PAT or OAuth flow\\n- [ ] `slopweaver connect slack` — Slack bot token flow (preview if OAuth UX isn't smooth)\\n- [ ] `slopweaver token create / list / revoke` — MCP token CRUD\\n- [ ] `slopweaver` (default command) — runs the local server on `localhost:60701` with stdio + HTTP MCP transports\\n- [ ] `slopweaver status` — service health + per-integration freshness\\n\\n## MCP tools (5 core + 2 diagnostic)\\n\\n- [ ] `start_session()` — **THE FLAGSHIP**. Searches across all integrations, returns prioritized list of what needs attention with reasoning\\n- [ ] `get_context_on(reference)` — generic \\\"what is this?\\\" investigation across integrations\\n- [ ] `get_pr_context(pr_url)` — specific case of `get_context_on` for PRs\\n- [ ] `catch_me_up(since)` — what changed while offline\\n- [ ] `search_work_context(query, filters?)` — full-text search over local evidence log\\n- [ ] `get_freshness()` — per-integration last-poll + stale flag (also returned inline on every primary tool)\\n- [ ] `ping()` — connection verification\\n\\n## Local web UI on `localhost:60701`\\n\\n- [ ] **Diagnostics** page — first-class onboarding UI; last poll times, integration health, MCP client connection status\\n- [ ] **Session view** — what `start_session()` returned most recently, browsable\\n- [ ] **Evidence Log Browser** — full-text search + filter + citation chips\\n- [ ] **Inbox** — unified deduplicated feed (minimal styling)\\n- [ ] **Settings** — integrations connect/disconnect, MCP token management, telemetry toggle\\n\\n## Packages (in roughly this order)\\n\\n- [ ] `packages/contracts/` — ts-rest + Zod API contracts (warm-up; small)\\n- [ ] `packages/env/` + `packages/config/` — env schemas + shared build configs\\n- [ ] `packages/db/` — Drizzle schemas (mcp-tokens, mcp-audit-log, workspaces, evidence-log, identity-graph) + SQLite migrations\\n- [ ] `packages/auth/` — MCP token CRUD + GitHub PAT helper\\n- [ ] `packages/mcp-server/` — framework-agnostic MCP server (stdio + HTTP), bearer auth, audit log with redaction, rate limiting, tool registry\\n- [ ] `packages/integrations/core/` + `packages/integrations/github/` — polling, OAuth, identity-graph hooks for GitHub\\n- [ ] `packages/mcp-server/src/tools/composite/start-session.ts` — flagship composite tool\\n- [ ] `packages/web-ui/` — React component library for the local UI\\n- [ ] `apps/mcp-local/` — CLI commands wiring everything into the binary\\n- [ ] `packages/integrations/slack/` — Slack integration\\n\\n## OSS infrastructure\\n\\n- [ ] `CONTRIBUTING.md` — short stub for now (project is pre-alpha; PRs welcome but expect iteration)\\n- [ ] `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` — Contributor Covenant 2.1\\n- [ ] `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/{bug_report,feature_request,integration_request}.yml`\\n- [ ] `.github/pull_request_template.md`\\n- [ ] GitHub Actions: `ci.yml` for lint + test + build on PRs\\n- [ ] GitHub Actions: `publish.yml` for npm publish on tag (granular npm tokens)\\n\\n## Pre-launch (founder action items)\\n\\n- [x] Reserve `slopweaver` npm name (v0.0.0 stub published)\\n- [x] New public repo created\\n- [ ] GitHub OAuth App for SlopWeaver Local (callback `http://localhost:60701/oauth/github/callback`)\\n- [ ] Slack App for SlopWeaver Local (bot token scopes)\\n- [ ] GitHub Sponsors application\\n\\n## Launch day\\n\\n- [ ] 60–90 second launch video (terminal + Claude Code + result)\\n- [ ] Submit to Official MCP Registry\\n- [ ] Submit to PulseMCP\\n- [ ] Submit to ≥2 awesome-mcp lists\\n- [ ] Publish Claude Code plugin marketplace.json (`/plugin marketplace add slopweaver/slopweaver`)\\n- [ ] Show HN (Tuesday/Wednesday US Eastern morning)\\n- [ ] X / Bluesky thread (founder voice — pivot lessons + demo)\\n- [ ] Discord cross-posts (Claude Code, Cursor, Cline, MCP communities)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success metric\\n\\n**100 users who successfully call `start_session` from an MCP client within 30 days of launch.** Stars are top of funnel; user-completing-the-flow is the real bottom-of-funnel metric.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope for v1.0.0\\n\\n- ❌ Named agents (no agent runtime in v1; Claude Code IS the agent)\\n- ❌ Mutations (read-only MCP tools only)\\n- ❌ Mobile / push notifications (year 2 cloud-tier)\\n- ❌ Cross-device sync (year 2)\\n- ❌ Webhook ingestion (year 2 — v1 polls)\\n- ❌ Cloud tier deployment (code may exist but not operated)\\n- ❌ Linear / Gmail / Calendar / DevOps integrations (v1.1+)\\n- ❌ Sign-up / onboarding wizard (zero signup; CLI prompts when needed)\\n- ❌ Any LLM-backed feature requiring BYOK (defer until first agent ships in v1.1)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## How to help\\n\\nIf you want to contribute, **wait until `CONTRIBUTING.md` lands** (early in this roadmap). For now:\\n\\n- ⭐ Star the repo to follow along\\n- 💬 Open a Discussion with feedback or use-case ideas\\n- 🪲 If you find a real bug in alpha builds, file an Issue (templates land soon)\\n- 🔒 Report security vulnerabilities privately (see [SECURITY.md](../blob/main/SECURITY.md))\\n\\n---\\n\\n_This issue is updated as items complete. Subscribe to follow along._\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/2/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11\",\"id\":4367852712,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBFgkqA\",\"number\":11,\"title\":\"Decision: OAuth 2.1 vs PAT for v1 auth model\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842931955,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkoC8w\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/decision-record\",\"name\":\"decision-record\",\"color\":\"5319e7\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"Design decision deliberated in public; closing comment = resolution\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestone/1\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/milestones/1/labels\",\"id\":15768380,\"node_id\":\"MI_kwDOSSFOvc4A8Js8\",\"number\":1,\"title\":\"v1.0.0\",\"description\":\"First public release of SlopWeaver. Help Claude Code answer 'what should I work on next?' by searching across your work tools. See tracking issue for the full checklist.\",\"creator\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"open_issues\":2,\"closed_issues\":1,\"state\":\"open\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:32Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:22Z\",\"due_on\":null,\"closed_at\":null},\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:10:11Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:22Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:13:22Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## Problem statement\\n\\nv1 of SlopWeaver-Local needs an auth mechanism so the local MCP server (running on \\\\`localhost:60701\\\\`) can authenticate requests from MCP clients (Claude Code, Cursor, Cline, browser-based MCP clients).\\n\\nTwo viable options. Both work. Tradeoffs differ. This issue is the public deliberation; closing comment captures the resolution.\\n\\n## Options considered\\n\\n### Option A: PAT (personal access token) — simpler\\n\\nUser runs \\\\`slopweaver token create my-laptop\\\\`, gets a long-lived bearer token (\\\\`slop_mcp_<24 hex>\\\\`), pastes it into \\\\`~/.claude.json\\\\` under \\\\`env.SLOPWEAVER_MCP_TOKEN\\\\`. From then on, MCP client sends \\\\`Authorization: Bearer slop_mcp_...\\\\` on every request.\\n\\n**Pros**:\\n- Minimal implementation — bcrypt-hashed at rest, simple verify on each request\\n- Familiar pattern (GitHub PAT, npm token, Heroku API token)\\n- Works with every MCP client without OAuth-flow support\\n- Headless / SSH / devbox friendly (no browser required)\\n\\n**Cons**:\\n- Long-lived; bigger blast radius if leaked (token stays valid until manual revoke)\\n- No automatic rotation\\n- User has to copy-paste a token string (UX papercut)\\n- Less secure than OAuth 2.1 in absolute terms\\n\\n### Option B: OAuth 2.1 with localhost callback\\n\\nSlopWeaver-Local runs an OAuth 2.1 server (using MCP SDK's \\\\`OAuthServerProvider\\\\` interface). User adds \\\\`{ \\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"http://localhost:60701\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"auth\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"oauth\\\\\\\" }\\\\` to MCP client config. First MCP invocation triggers OAuth flow: browser opens → \\\\\\\"Allow Claude Code to access SlopWeaver?\\\\\\\" → click → MCP client receives access + refresh tokens → auto-refreshes thereafter.\\n\\n**Pros**:\\n- Auto-rotation via refresh tokens — short-lived access tokens limit blast radius\\n- Industry standard, battle-tested patterns (PKCE, scope grants, revocation)\\n- MCP ecosystem direction — the MCP SDK has substantial OAuth scaffolding\\n- Better UX (browser \\\\\\\"Allow\\\\\\\" vs copy-paste token string)\\n- Same auth model as v2 cloud-tier; no migration needed\\n- More security-conscious posture for the senior IC engineer audience\\n\\n**Cons**:\\n- Significantly more implementation work in v1\\n- MCP SDK's OAuth server requires Express dep (or substantial reimplementation)\\n- Doesn't help vs full filesystem compromise (both access + refresh tokens stored in same config file)\\n- Headless / SSH / devbox users need a device-code fallback (or OAuth flow doesn't work)\\n- Some MCP clients may not yet support \\\\`auth: \\\\\\\"oauth\\\\\\\"\\\\` config\\n\\n### Option C: Hybrid — both\\n\\nShip PAT as the default, OAuth 2.1 as an opt-in advanced flow.\\n\\n**Pros**: covers all audiences.\\n**Cons**: maintain two auth code paths from day one; more surface area.\\n\\n## Recommendation (proposer's view — open to pushback)\\n\\n**Option B (OAuth 2.1)** as the v1 default, with PAT available as a fallback for headless/SSH users.\\n\\nReasoning:\\n1. Founder is security-conscious and explicitly raised this as a concern (\\\\\\\"PATs are less secure\\\\\\\")\\n2. OAuth is where the MCP ecosystem is heading; designing now avoids a migration in year 2\\n3. The UX is genuinely better (no copy-paste)\\n4. The MCP SDK does most of the work via \\\\`OAuthServerProvider\\\\` — implementation is bounded\\n5. PAT can be a small addition (\\\\`--auth=pat\\\\` flag in \\\\`slopweaver init\\\\`) for the headless case\\n\\nBut Option A is a defensible v1 choice if implementation budget is tight or if MCP client OAuth support turns out to be patchy in practice (worth investigating — see resources below).\\n\\n## Relevant resources\\n\\n- MCP SDK auth: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk/tree/main/src/server/auth\\n- Claude Code MCP config docs: https://docs.claude.com/en/docs/claude-code/mcp (verify whether \\\\`auth: \\\\\\\"oauth\\\\\\\"\\\\` is supported in current CC versions)\\n- RFC 8628 (Device Authorization Grant — fallback for headless OAuth)\\n- Past discussion: closed PR #7 raised this; this issue captures the deliberation moving forward\\n\\n## Who needs to weigh in\\n\\n- Founder (decides)\\n- Anyone who's implemented OAuth 2.1 server-side recently (welcome to comment)\\n\\n## What needs investigating before deciding\\n\\n- [ ] Does Claude Code's current version support \\\\`auth: \\\\\\\"oauth\\\\\\\"\\\\` for local MCP servers? (Need to verify.)\\n- [ ] Does Cursor? Cline? (Lower priority but worth knowing.)\\n- [ ] What's the device-code fallback story — does the MCP SDK provide it, or do we implement?\\n- [ ] Implementation estimate: how many days for OAuth server vs PAT?\\n\\nRun \\\\`/investigate <topic>\\\\` against any of the above before this gets decided.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/11/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12\",\"id\":4370993656,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBIgR-A\",\"number\":12,\"title\":\"feat(cli-tools): add `pnpm cli doctor` subcommand + Vitest scaffolding\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"},{\"id\":10842930893,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-zQ\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/scaffolding\",\"name\":\"scaffolding\",\"color\":\"1d76db\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"Repo scaffolding / DevOps / AI orchestration work\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T05:47:20Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:57Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:57Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"### What needs to be done\\n\\nAdd the first interactive subcommand to `@slopweaver/cli-tools` (`pnpm cli doctor`) and stand up the Vitest infrastructure that future subcommands will hang off. Two-in-one PR because they're co-required: scaffolding alone has nothing to test, and a tested subcommand requires the scaffolding.\\n\\n`doctor` is an environment health check:\\n- Node version ≥ 22\\n- pnpm version ≥ 10\\n- Port 60701 free (the local API port)\\n- `~/.slopweaver/` data dir exists and is writable\\n\\nIf the data dir is missing, `doctor` prompts interactively to create it (demonstrates the `@inquirer/prompts` pattern future subcommands can reuse).\\n\\n### Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] `pnpm cli doctor` runs and exits 0 on a healthy machine\\n- [ ] Each check reports `ok` / `warn` / `fail` with a short detail line\\n- [ ] Failing data-dir check prompts to create it; on confirm, `mkdir -p` runs and the check re-reports\\n- [ ] Exit code 1 if any check fails (after any prompted fixes)\\n- [ ] Vitest installed; `pnpm test` from root runs the cli-tools suite via Turbo\\n- [ ] `@inquirer/prompts` and `picocolors` added as runtime deps\\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: `sanitiseTaskName`, `findMonorepoRoot`/`resolveWorktreesRoot`, `resolveDataDir`, all four doctor checks\\n- [ ] README updated with the `### doctor` section and the colocated `*.test.ts` convention\\n- [ ] CI green (`format:check` + `lint` + `compile` + `test`)\\n- [ ] No regression of `pnpm cli worktree new`\\n\\n### Context\\n\\nSub-task of #10 (Scaffolding & DevOps tracking) — picks up two of its checklist items in one PR (`pnpm cli doctor` + Vitest scaffolding for cli-tools).\\n\\nRelevant files:\\n- `packages/cli-tools/src/cli.ts` — register the new subcommand here\\n- `packages/cli-tools/src/worktree/index.ts` — pattern reference for `runX(...)` exports + `spawnSync` usage\\n- `packages/cli-tools/src/lib/paths.ts` — existing helpers to reuse and test\\n- `packages/cli-tools/README.md` — doc the new convention\\n\\nConventions established by this PR (set precedent for the next subcommand):\\n- One subcommand per dir under `src/<name>/` with `index.ts` exporting `run<Name>(...)`\\n- Pure functions in sibling files (`checks.ts` etc.) — easy to unit-test\\n- Tests colocated as `*.test.ts` next to the file under test (vs the private repo's `__tests__/` layout — colocation is more discoverable for a package this size)\\n- Interactive prompts via `@inquirer/prompts` (no custom wrapper); inject a `prompt` dep in tests\\n- Color via `picocolors`; subprocess via `node:child_process` `spawnSync` with `stdio: 'inherit'`\\n- Shared helpers in `src/lib/`\\n\\nDeliberately NOT in scope: `connect-local` (blocked on missing `apps/mcp-local` + OAuth + token store), an auto-fix mode beyond the data-dir prompt, root-level Vitest config, npm-publish decision (still open in #10), `--json` output flag.\\n\\n### AI agent prompt (copy-paste into Claude Code)\\n\\n```\\n/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/ISSUE-NUMBER\\n```\\n\\n### Are you taking this on yourself?\\n\\nI'm filing this; happy for an agent or contributor to pick it up.\\n\\nrefs #10\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/12/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15\",\"id\":4371016531,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBIhrUw\",\"number\":15,\"title\":\"fix(cli-tools): `pnpm cli worktree new` silently exits — cac multi-word commands don't fire actions\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842289141,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkAz9Q\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"d73a4a\",\"default\":true,\"description\":\"Something isn't working\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T06:01:39Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:56Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:56Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What's happening\\n\\n`pnpm cli worktree new <name>` exits 0 with no output and never creates the worktree.\\n\\n```\\n$ pnpm cli worktree new fix-issue-12\\n> slopweaver-monorepo@0.0.0 cli /Users/lachiejames/dev/slopweaver\\n> tsx packages/cli-tools/src/cli.ts \\\"worktree\\\" \\\"new\\\" \\\"fix-issue-12\\\"\\n$ echo $?\\n0\\n$ ls ~/dev/worktrees/fix-issue-12\\nls: ~/dev/worktrees/fix-issue-12: No such file or directory\\n```\\n\\n`pnpm cli --help` correctly lists the command, so registration looks fine — but the action callback never fires.\\n\\n## Root cause\\n\\ncac 7.0.0 doesn't support multi-word command names. `cli.command('worktree new <name>', ...)` registers the command for the help screen but `cli.parse()` won't match `worktree new <something>` as an invocation — `parsed.matchedCommand` is `undefined` and the action never fires.\\n\\nReproduced minimally:\\n\\n```js\\nimport { cac } from 'cac';\\nconst cli = cac('test');\\ncli.command('foo bar <name>', 'multi-word')\\n  .action((name) => console.log('FIRED:', name));\\ncli.parse(['node', 'script', 'foo', 'bar', 'baz']);\\n// → no output. Should print \\\"FIRED: baz\\\".\\n```\\n\\nSingle-word commands (`cli.command('foo <name>', ...)`) work fine.\\n\\nThis means the `worktree new` command has been silently broken since #8 landed — the help text suggests it works, so the regression is invisible until you actually try to create a worktree.\\n\\n## Fix options (one of)\\n\\n1. **Switch to a single-word command name**, e.g. `worktree-new <name>`. Smallest diff.\\n2. **Manually parse the subcommand** inside a single `worktree <subcommand> <name>` action.\\n3. **Switch CLI framework** — citty, clipanion, or commander all support nested subcommands natively. Heavier change; probably not warranted for one subcommand.\\n4. **Upgrade cac** if a newer version supports multi-word commands. (Not yet checked.)\\n\\nRecommend (1): rename to `pnpm cli worktree-new <name>`. Update README, root package.json scripts (none currently reference it), and `.claude/rules/workflow.md` (mentions `pnpm cli worktree new fix-issue-42` in two places).\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] `pnpm cli worktree-new fix-issue-N` (or chosen replacement) creates the worktree and produces the expected output\\n- [ ] `pnpm cli --help` shows the new spelling\\n- [ ] README + workflow.md updated\\n- [ ] Add a regression test that exercises the dispatcher (or at least asserts cac matches the registered command)\\n\\n## Workaround until fixed\\n\\nRun the underlying git command directly:\\n\\n```bash\\ngit -C ~/dev/slopweaver fetch origin main\\ngit -C ~/dev/slopweaver worktree add -b worktree/<name> ~/dev/worktrees/<name> origin/main\\n(cd ~/dev/worktrees/<name> && pnpm install)\\n```\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/15/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13\",\"id\":4370997479,\"node_id\":\"I_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAABBIgg5w\",\"number\":13,\"title\":\"ci: add release.yml for npm publish on GitHub Release\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"id\":10842930866,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-sg\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/task\",\"name\":\"task\",\"color\":\"0e8a16\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"AI-actionable unit of work; one issue = one PR\"},{\"id\":10842930893,\"node_id\":\"LA_kwDOSSFOvc8AAAAChkn-zQ\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/labels/scaffolding\",\"name\":\"scaffolding\",\"color\":\"1d76db\",\"default\":false,\"description\":\"Repo scaffolding / DevOps / AI orchestration work\"}],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T05:50:03Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:14Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:14Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"sub_issues_summary\":{\"total\":0,\"completed\":0,\"percent_completed\":0},\"issue_dependencies_summary\":{\"blocked_by\":0,\"total_blocked_by\":0,\"blocking\":0,\"total_blocking\":0},\"body\":\"## What needs to be done\\n\\nAdd a GitHub Actions workflow `release.yml` that publishes the workspace's non-private packages to npm when a GitHub Release is published. The workflow ships dormant — `pnpm -r publish` automatically skips `private: true` packages, so the workflow is a safe no-op until a package is flipped to publishable.\\n\\nSub-task of #10 (Scaffolding & DevOps tracking → DevOps → \\\"GitHub Actions: `release.yml` for npm publish on tag\\\").\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/release.yml` added\\n- [ ] Triggers: `release: [published]` and `workflow_dispatch` (with a `dry_run` boolean input, default `true`)\\n- [ ] Runs on `ubuntu-latest` (free GitHub-hosted runner — not Blacksmith)\\n- [ ] Action versions pinned to commit SHAs with version comment (e.g. `actions/checkout@<sha> # v4`)\\n- [ ] Minimal `permissions:` block — `contents: read`, `id-token: write` (for npm provenance + Trusted Publisher OIDC)\\n- [ ] Manual approval gate via `environment: npm-publish`\\n- [ ] `concurrency: { group: release, cancel-in-progress: false }`\\n- [ ] Same gates CI runs (`pnpm format:check / lint / compile / test`) execute before publish\\n- [ ] Publish step uses `pnpm -r publish --access public --provenance --no-git-checks`\\n- [ ] No `NPM_TOKEN` secret — relies on npm Trusted Publisher OIDC\\n- [ ] `RELEASING.md` runbook added at repo root: one-time setup (npm Trusted Publisher + GitHub `npm-publish` environment), per-release steps, dry-run instructions, rollback note (`npm deprecate`)\\n- [ ] CI green (`pnpm format:check / lint / compile / test`)\\n- [ ] PR refs (not closes) #10 — issue #10 is a tracking parent\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nConstraints from the founder:\\n- Take inspiration from the private repo's release pipeline (`~/dev/slopweaver-private/.github/workflows/deploy-production.yml`) for security shape (pinned SHAs, environment protection, minimal permissions, native Release event trigger), but **much simpler** — npm publish only, no native apps, no Tauri, no app stores.\\n- Free GitHub runners, not Blacksmith.\\n- Repo is public → security-first.\\n\\nOut of scope for this PR (file as separate work):\\n- Flipping `@slopweaver/cli-tools` from `private: true` to publishable (open decision on #10)\\n- Changesets / release-please / any version-bump tooling — manual `pnpm version` is fine for one publishable package\\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — GitHub Release notes serve that role for v1\\n- Slack / Sentry / smoke-test post-publish steps\\n- GitHub Packages mirror\\n\\nRelevant files for the implementer:\\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — mirror its setup style (Node via `.nvmrc`, pnpm via `pnpm/action-setup@v4`, cache)\\n- `.nvmrc` and root `package.json` `engines` — Node 22 / pnpm 10\\n- `pnpm-workspace.yaml` — confirms what `pnpm -r publish` will scan\\n\\n## AI agent prompt (copy-paste into Claude Code)\\n\\n```\\n/fix-issue https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/ISSUE-NUMBER\\n```\\n\\n## Are you taking this on yourself?\\n\\nI'm filing this; happy for an agent or contributor to pick it up\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/13/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":\"completed\",\"pinned_comment\":null,\"score\":1}],\"search_type\":\"lexical\"}"
